Hello, everybody. Hello and welcome.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.530
Thank you so much. Thank you.

00:34.730 --> 00:37.290
I am often asked,
well, I am sometimes asked,

00:37.770 --> 00:39.890
well, actually,
I was once asked by one person,

00:40.410 --> 00:44.330
why we review fast Vauxhalls
so rarely on Top Gear.

00:45.410 --> 00:47.930
The simple answer -
they're terrible rubbish.

00:48.450 --> 00:52.410
Vauxhall, however, has just
introduced a new fast Astra

00:53.050 --> 00:54.850
and says it isn't terrible rubbish.

00:56.650 --> 00:57.450
Hmmm.

01:02.730 --> 01:04.970
It's called the VXR and on paper,

01:05.370 --> 01:07.610
it certainly appears to be
terrible rubbish.

01:11.210 --> 01:13.850
Because what they've done,
bless them, is fit under the bonnet

01:14.250 --> 01:16.490
of a front-wheel drive
Vauxhall Astra,

01:16.850 --> 01:19.250
a 276 horsepower engine.

01:22.730 --> 01:27.490
That's as daft as fitting the heart-
of an elephant in a mouse.

01:31.850 --> 01:34.090
The thing is, the front wheels
have to do the steering

01:34.330 --> 01:36.410
and that's a big, important job.

01:36.810 --> 01:40.730
And asking them
to handle 276 horsepower as well,

01:41.290 --> 01:44.650
means you've to do some
very, very clever engineering.

01:49.490 --> 01:50.330
Not that long ago,

01:50.730 --> 01:54.930
Vauxhall was making the not-at-all
cleverly engineered Vectra.

01:55.410 --> 01:59.650
The most dreary, uninspiring
car in all of human history.

02:02.130 --> 02:03.490
Oh!

02:04.890 --> 02:06.850
It really was a cure for ADD.

02:07.210 --> 02:09.371
If you put a hyperactive child
in there, he'd be asleep

02:09.410 --> 02:11.490
in three minutes flat.
I mean, look at it!

02:13.010 --> 02:15.090
It's as gripping
as a Victorian novel,

02:15.490 --> 02:17.730
as stylish as a taxman's trousers.

02:18.250 --> 02:21.210
You almost got the impression
they designed it in a coffee break.

02:22.250 --> 02:24.650
Oh, quick, the boss wants
a new car. There's one.

02:25.410 --> 02:26.690
Give it some fancy door mirrors.

02:26.770 --> 02:29.010
It'll look like we made
an effort. They hadn't!

02:30.530 --> 02:33.050
So the idea that a company
which did this,

02:33.570 --> 02:37.650
now thinks it has the technical
ability to put 276 horsepowers

02:38.170 --> 02:40.970
through the front wheels of
a hatchback is laughable.

02:43.850 --> 02:45.250
The thing is though, amazingly,

02:45.650 --> 02:46.770
they've pulled it off!

